Added external protocol support for XMODEM, YMODEM, YMODEM-g, and ZMODEM:

If C-K is built with -DCK_XYZ it has protocol selections of Kermit, Zmodem,
Ymodem, Ymodem-g, and Xmodem.  In the OS/2 and Windows versions, the XYZ
protocols are internal.  In other versions they are external and the user
must define the associated commands; in any case, this feature is available
only in implementations that support CK_REDIR (the REDIRECT command).

  set protocol <name> [ <autouploadcmd> [ <sendcmd> [ <rcvcmd> ] ] ]

If command stops after <name>, the protocol is selected but nothing else
is changed.

The remaining fields are commands that apply to the given protocol.  They work
like this:

The <autouploadcmd> is the command to send to the host when commencing an
upload, for example "rz" when sending with Zmodem.

The last two commands, <sendcmd> and <rcvcmd>, are only for use with external
protocols.

If a <...cmd> is given, it replaces the previous one, if any.  To include a
command that has embedded spaces, enclose it in { braces }.  To erase a
command, use {} (empty braces).

If you specify one command, you must specify all three, otherwise the trailing
ones will be erased.

Each of these commands may include "%s" (percent sign followed by lowercase s)
which will be substituted by the filename(s) in your SEND or RECEIVE command.
Example:

  set protocol zmodem rz {sz %s} rz
  set protocol xmodem {rx %s} {sx %x} {rx %s}
  set protocol zmodem {} {sz %s} rz

The defaults are:

  set protocol zmodem {} {sz %s} rz
  set protocol ymodem {} {sb %s} rb
  set protocol ymodem-g {} {sb %s} rb
  set protocol xmodem {} {sx %x} {rx %s}
  set protocol kermit {}

Since Kermit does not understand the syntax of external protocol programs
there is no way for it to modify the external commands automatically to make
their options agree with Kermit's own (e.g. text vs binary mode, send vs
resend).  However, since you, the user, understand the syntax of your external
protocol, it should not be difficult for you to write macros to do this;
e.g. for Zmodem:

  def sz {
    local \%p \%t
    asg \%p \v(protocol)               ; Save current protocol
    if = \v(ftype) text asg \%t -a     ; sz text-mode option
    set proto zmodem rz {sz \%t %s} rz ; Choose zmodem in text or binary mode
    send \%1                           ; Send the file
    asg \%t \v(status)                 ; Save file-transfer status
    set proto \%p                      ; Restore protocol
    end \%t                            ; Return file-transfer status
  }

Warning: when used in conjunction with Add, there is no way to accommodate
mixed text/binary mode transfers when using external protocols.

Another note: If you want to use a protocol other than the ones listed, just
lie about its name and define the appropriate commands.

