Added SET PRINTER to UNIX and other versions, as in OS/2, etc.  However, it
will have no effect in VMS, VOS, etc, until zprint() functions in ck*fio.c
are updated to use it.  NOTE: In Windows and VMS, a filename is used as the
printer (PRN, LPT:).  In UNIX, there is a distinction between a filename and
a pipe -- in UNIX a pipe must be used to run a program; if a pipe is not
given, the value is regarded as a filename.  So:

  set printer |lpr            ; Uses the lpr program for printing.
  set printer {| lpr -Pblah}  ; Ditto, with options (braces needed for spaces)
  set printer foo.x           ; A file
  set printer                 ; Restore default value

