Started work on redirection of text received in response to a REMOTE
command.  Syntax is simply "> file" at the end of any REMOTE command:

  remote blah blah [ > file ]      (write to file)

or:

  remote blah blah [ | command ]   (pipe to command)

or:

  remote blah blah [ | command > file ]

(The parsing of this part is done, but not the action -- ckuus7.c.)

This is complicated, however, by the fact that the REMOTE HOST command
itself may contain or end with redirection or pipe indications, so new
syntax is needed to indicate "which end" it applies to:

  remote host blah blah [ > file ]             This end
  remote host { blah blah } [ > file ]         This end
  remote host { blah blah > file }             That end
  remote host { blah blah > file } > file      Both ends

