Added implementation of GET-PATH to gnfile() ("get next file").  If a SERVER
GET-PATH is set, then it, and only it, is used.  Thus, if you also want Kermit
to look in its current directory when a GET-PATH is in effect, the current
directory must be included in the GET-PATH.  If the client sends an absolute
(fully qualified) pathname, that takes precedence over the GET-PATH.  If it
sends a relative pathname (or simply a filename), then the directories in
the GET-PATH are searched, in the order given, and the file is sent from the
first directory in which it is found; if it is not found in any of them, a
