Added auotupload to the UNIX version.  It's simple.  Instead of only looking
for an S packet, we also look for an I packet.  If we get one, we go into
server mode instead of receive mode, and we set a flag that says that when
the transfer is complete, i.e. after the B packet has been sent and ACK'd,
that instead of going back to server command wait, we (reset the flag and)
