There has always been the horrible bug in VMS C-Kermit that the SEND and OPEN
READ file shared the same RMS channel.  Thus you could not send a file and
have an OPEN READ file at the same time.  If you closed one, it would close
the other, etc.  So I tried to fix this by cloning ALL of the fab/rab/xab/blab
structures and and buffers and pointers and routines and code (I'm sure there
must be a better way but I'm not a VMS programmer).  In so doing, I noticed
that the filesize for a SEND file was being set in zchki() rather than
zopeni(), and so if this ever worked, it was purely by accident, since how do
we know that the file we are sending is the one we most recently zchki'd?  So
I moved and separated all of the size getting to the appropriate places.
Anyway finally I got it all done and working.  Really gross.  But it's better
now, at least because (for example) zchin() no longer ASSUMES it is reading
from ZIFILE.  Test: make a file containing a list of filenames.  Then write a
command file that opens the other file, reads a line at a time into a
variable, and then sends the file whose name is in the variable, then TAKE
the command file.  Works OK.  CKVFIO.C, 21 Aug 96.

