Peter Eichhorn noticed that dialing stopped suddenly on HP-UX right after
Kermit told the modem to use RTS/CTS.  That's because, even though Kermit had
been told to "set flow rts/cts" (or auto), it does not actually take affect
until after dialing is complete.  So if RTS was not being asserted (as it was
not in this case), the modem would never send any more characters back to the
computer, and dialing would fail.  Tentative solution: add a new low-level
communications routine, ttsetflow(), to ckutio.c; document it in ckcplm.doc.
Call it from ckudia.c just after the aforementioned modem command returns OK.
Put the call within #ifdef CK_TTSETFLOW..#endif.  In ckcdeb.h, define
CK_TTSETFLOW for UNIX.  If this works out, maybe we can use this routine in
a lot of other places for simplification and sanity.  21 Sep 96.

