Fixed a bug that has been bugging me for years.  On some Telnet connections,
it is necessary to SET PARITY SPACE for file transfer to succeed (because the
Telnet connection itself is not 8-bit clean).  However, once you transfer a
file, Telnet negotiations don't work any more -- even though they did before.
This is most often noticed after logging out and then trying to log back in
again (since Telnet negotiations *usually* happen only at the beginning of a
session).  The fix was rather complicated, involving most tt*() routines in
ckutio.c, plus ckcgetc() in ckucon.c, plus calls to tn_doop() in ckucon.c.
Basically, parity-stripping was moved up to a higher level.  We always do it
during packet operations, but, on TELNET connections only, in CONNECT mode
(and INPUT, etc) we do it only after first checking for IAC and passing
negotiations along to tn_doop().  20 Oct 96.

