Working on VMS C-Kermit problem with re-CONNECT-ing to a Telnet host that
had previously closed the connection.  This should open a new one, but it
never has.  Added debugging statements, tried lots of experiments.  Found
that various VMS routines, including ttchk(), nettchk(), ck_cancio(), 
contti(), etc, did not check for "connection not open" before calling the
system.  Each time I added one of these checks, I got a little farther, but
only to reveal another gotcha.  To be continued...  26 Oct 96.

Changes for BEBOX to ckcnet.h, to let it use the TCPIPLIB code.  27 Oct 96.

Hellmuth Michaelis at Hanseatischer Computerservice GmbH in Hamburg pointed
