The connection itself was at 31200bps.  C-Kermit sent itself (the kermit
binary) at 4100 cps.  Later, on a 28800bps connection, it received a 1.2MB
compressed file at 2960 cps.  RTS/CTS was totally effective; modem lights
would blink in lockstep, and there were no retransmissions in either
direction.  SET CARRIER-WATCH ON works fine, too.  9 Nov 96.

